1 olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 beetroot
2 clove garlic
1 packet roasted almonds
¼ tsp salt
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 tsp honey
20 g butter
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 sachet Creole spice blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut onion into wedges. Cut carrot and parsnip
into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small
chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Roughly chop
roasted almonds.
• In a large bowl, combine Creole spice blend, the
salt and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add pork loin steaks and turn to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, cook
pork until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each
side (cook in batches if your pan is getting
crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and
turn pork to coat.
• Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: Don't worry if your pork gets a little charred
during cooking. It adds to the flavour!

• While the pork is cooking, heat the butter in a
medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook
garlic, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder
and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous and stir to combine, then cover
with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside until
the water is absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with
a fork.

• When the couscous is done, add roasted veggies
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Stir to
combine and season to taste.

• Slice Creole pork.
• Divide roast veggie couscous between bowls.
Top with pork and garlic dip.
• Garnish with roasted almonds to serve. Enjoy!